text.section:
Unless authorized by the Maryland Insurance Commissioner to engage in the insurance business in the State, a warrantor may not use the following words in its name, contracts, or literature:
"Insurance";
"Casualty";
"Surety";
"Mutual"; or
Any other words that are:
Descriptive of the insurance, casualty, or surety business; or
Deceptively similar to the name or description of an insurer, a surety corporation, or another warrantor.
